post_text: Community Building Activity: The Bobcat Behavior Team would love to hear about how you celebrated or plan to celebrate Earth Day! Hopefully during your home learning time, you are getting outside and enjoying nature. As citizens of our New Boston community and of our Earth, we have a responsibility to keep our community clean and to not waste resources. Show us how you are being responsible! Attached is a flower template for you to decorate. In the petals or around the flower, please write or draw about ways that you can be responsible and help our environment. When you're done with your flower, take a picture and load it to this form:https://forms.gle/7QXKpwjg72a5N6ry8 by Thursday, April 30th. You may also send a photo showing your Earth Day spirit, We will put all of the flowers/photos together into a slide show to share with all of you!

post_text:
Kindergarten/1st Grade Registration:

It is time to register children entering either Kindergarten or 1st Grade in the 2020-21 school year now!

Kindergarten/Readiness/First Parent Information Nights
We will be sponsoring a Parent Information Night for the
parents of incoming Kindergarten, Readiness and First Grade Students in April. Letters will be mailed home to families in Mid-March. It will be helpful if we have your schild’s information/registration in order to assure you will receive the parent letter. Thank you in advance for registering your students for the 2020-2021 school year.
To register your students you may stop by the office or go to our website, www.nbcs.k12.nh.us, and print off the registration documents.
You also can scan in your documents and email them to rachael.spray@sau19.org. (If your child already attends NBCS you do not need to do anything.)

post_text:
Destination Imagination Info Night
Imagine a system of learning in which students develop the ability to think critically and creatively, learn how to work together to achieve goals, listen, evaluate, and build upon teammate’s ideas, manage time, persevere, and HAVE FUN! Destination Imagination teaches the creative process from imagination to innovation.

NBCS is looking to expand the Destination Imagination program to students grades K-6th. There will be an information night on Tuesday, September 24th @ 6:00pm in the New Boston Central School library for parents and their child(ren) to attend and learn more about this amazing program. If you cannot attend the meeting but would like your child(ren) to participate, please contact Theresa Elliott at theresa.elliott@sau19.org.

post_text:
The bus routes for the 2019-2020 school year are attached below. For ease of viewing we have listed the routes in the following categories: If your child resides in New Boston and is attending Goffstown High School, the route will be listed as NBCS-GHS-AM PM.. If your child is a NBCS student or MVMS Student the AM route will be listed as NBCS-MVMS- AM. If your child attends NBCS the PM route will be listed as NBCS PM

**Please note that New Boston MVMS students travel with the high school students in the P.M. in which case their route would be listed under NBCS-GHS-MVMS P.M.**

post_text: Some of the cool things our PTA has been doing this week for our students.
shared_text:
New Boston Central School PTA
May 29, 2019 at 8:19 PM ·

The PTA has been busy with Curriculum Enrichment Programs this week! The 1st graders went to "Pete the Cat" at Capitol Center of the Arts, the 2nd graders learned about seed dispersement from a representative from the Audubon Center and the 3rd graders were visited by a giant whale from the New England Aquarium! A special thank you to Julie Kirklin and Karen Roach for their hard work coordinating these and many other amazing events all year long!!
